末.definition: tip; end; final stage; latter part; inessential detail; powder; dust; opera role of old man

末了.definition: (coll.) final part; last bit; (coll.) in the end; finally

末代皇帝.definition: The Last Emperor, 1987 biopic of Pu Yi 溥儀|溥仪[Pu3 yi2] by Bernardo Bertolucci

末任.definition: (of the holder of an official post which no longer exists) the last (incumbent)

末伏.definition: the third of the three annual periods of hot weather (三伏[san1 fu2]), which typically runs over the middle ten days of August

末位淘汰.definition: sacking the worst-performing employee; elimination of the worst-performing contestant

末席.definition: end seat; place for less senior person

末座.definition: end seat; final place (for less senior person)

末日.definition: last day; end; final days; doomsday

末期.definition: end (of a period); last part; final phase

末班車.definition: last bus or train; last chance

末葉.definition: final years; end (of a decade, era etc)

末藥.definition: myrrh (Commiphora myrrha); also written 沒藥|没药[mo4 yao4]

末路.definition: dead end; impasse; end of the road; final days

末速.definition: speed at the end of the trajectory; speed in the final stage

末願.definition: final vows (in a religious order or congregation of the Catholic Church)
